        <h3>Four things are enough.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>A → B points and any meaningful stops in between;</li>
          <li>date and preferred start time;</li>
          <li>passengers and luggage volume;</li>
          <li>vehicle class or format preferences — if any.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="contact-block">
        <p class="eyebrow">What you get back</p>
        <h3>A confirmed route, before departure.</h3>
        <p>One route with timing by checkpoints. One price in one message. An agreed format for the meeting and the on-road communication. No "let's see later" — if anything changes, you hear it first.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

